  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO BRING FORWARD SECTIONS 71-7-1 THROUGH 71-7-15 AND 71-7-19 THROUGH 71-7-33, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972, WHICH AUTHORIZE PUBLIC AND PRIVATE EMPLOYERS TO VOLUNTARILY ELECT TO CONDUCT DRUG AND ALCOHOL TESTING OF EMPLOYEES, FOR PURPOSES OF POSSIBLE AMENDMENT; TO BRING FORWARD SECTION 47-5-196, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972, WHICH REQUIRES THE MISSISSIPPI DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS TO CONDUCT MANDATORY DRUG TESTING OF ITS EMPLOYEES, FOR PURPOSES OF POSSIBLE AMENDMENT; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
